SNRZDMg65PuYWAEQgKe6a\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01GZqGkQtHB58eVVTcpTZqa8\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-axon-dccbdf73-20260415T013041-1340da9f/crates/axon-core/src/auth.rs\",\"offset\":0,\"limit\":400},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"stop_details\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":6,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":567,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":29402,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":567,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01TSMSYvQzdh78YH3Sxyiy8q\",\"session_id\":\"80f0eb9d-4064-4d06-8560-e247ce1170f2\",\"uuid\":\"e352c111-d313-465c-87e6-a2f60ebf2a3e\"}\n{\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"task_progress\",\"task_id\":\"ab7893c6e8bebbea1\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01TSMSYvQzdh78YH3Sxyiy8q\",\"description\":\"Reading crates/axon-core/src/auth.rs\",\"usage\":{\"total_tokens\":30022,\"tool_uses\":20,\"duration_ms\":15377},\"last_tool_name\":\"Read\",\"uuid\":\"f68a9f62-9f52-4923-ad35-e30bd917ebb5\",\"session_id\":\"80f0eb9d-4064-4d06-8560-e247ce1170f2\"}\n{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_011SNRZDMg65PuYWAEQgKe6a\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_017xXnEF67K9wcoU5PYR97aD\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-axon-dccbdf73-20260415T013041-1340da9f/crates/axon-core/src/auth.rs\",\"offset\":400,\"limit\":500},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"stop_details\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":6,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":567,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":29402,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":567,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01TSMSYvQzdh78YH3Sxyiy8q\",\"session_id\":\"80f0eb9d-4064-4d06-8560-e247ce1170f2\",\"uuid\":\"92b47ace-996f-434b-8094-8824e2752669\"}\n{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01GZqGkQtHB58eVVTcpTZqa8\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"0\\t//! Role-based and attribute-based access control for Axon (FEAT-012).\\n1\\t//!\\n2\\t//! # Layers\\n3\\t//!\\n4\\t//! **Layer 1 — RBAC** ([`Role`], [`CallerIdentity`], [`Operation`])\\n5\\t//!\\n6\\t//! Four built-in roles (`Admin \u003e Write \u003e Read \u003e None`) control access to\\n7\\t//! Axon operations.  Roles are derived from the identity provider (Tailscale\\n8\\t//! ACL tags, OIDC claims, etc.) by the server layer and passed into handlers\\n9\\t//! as a [`CallerIdentity`].  Handlers call [`CallerIdentity::check`] to\\n10\\t//! enforce the minimum required role.\\n11\\t//!\\n12\\t//! **Layer 2 — Field-level masking** ([`MaskPolicy`])\\n13\\t//!\\n14\\t//! A `MaskPolicy` hides individual entity fields from callers whose role\\n15\\t//! falls below a configured minimum.  Applied by [`CallerIdentity::apply_masks`]\\n16\\t//! before returning entity data to the caller.  Admins always see all fields.\\n17\\t//!\\n18\\t//! **Layer 3 — Collection write control** ([`WritePolicy`])\\n19\\t//!\\n20\\t//! A `WritePolicy` sets a per-collection minimum write role and marks fields\\n21\\t//! as immutable after creation.  Checked by the handler before any mutation.\\n22\\t//!\\n23\\t//! **Layer 4 — Database-scoped grants** ([`DatabaseGrant`], [`GrantRegistry`])\\n24\\t//!\\n25\\t//! Grants scope a role to a specific database (or `\\\"*\\\"` for all databases).\\n26\\t//! Without a matching grant a caller has `Role::None` on that database.\\n27\\t//! Admins with a global grant bypass per-database checks.  The grant registry\\n28\\t//! is stored in `__axon_policies__` and enforced at the routing layer.\\n29\\t\\n30\\tuse serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};\\n31\\t\\n32\\tuse crate::error::AxonError;\\n33\\t\\n34\\t/// Built-in roles for Axon RBAC (FEAT-012).\\n35\\t///\\n36\\t/// Roles are ordered by privilege: `Admin \u003e Write \u003e Read \u003e None`.\\n37\\t/// When a user has multiple roles (e.g., from multiple ACL tags),\\n38\\t/// the highest-privilege role wins.\\n39\\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, PartialOrd, Ord, Hash, Serialize, Deserialize)]\\n40\\tpub enum Role {\\n41\\t    /// No access. Explicitly denied.\\n42\\t    None = 0,\\n43\\t    /// Read entities, query, traverse, browse audit log.\\n44\\t    Read = 1,\\n45\\t    /// Create, update, delete entities and links in any collection.\\n46\\t    Write = 2,\\n47\\t    /// All operations including drop and schema changes.\\n48\\t    Admin = 3,\\n49\\t}\\n50\\t\\n51\\timpl Role {\\n52\\t    /// Parse a role from a Tailscale ACL tag or string name.\\n53\\t    ///\\n54\\t    /// Accepted inputs (both full `tag:` prefix and bare name):\\n55\\t    ///\\n56\\t    /// | Input | Role |\\n57\\t    /// |-------|------|\\n58\\t    /// | `\\\"tag:axon-admin\\\"` / `\\\"tag:admin\\\"` / `\\\"admin\\\"` | `Admin` |\\n59\\t    /// | `\\\"tag:axon-write\\\"` / `\\\"tag:axon-agent\\\"` / `\\\"tag:write\\\"` / `\\\"write\\\"` | `Write` |\\n60\\t    /// | `\\\"tag:axon-read\\\"` / `\\\"tag:read\\\"` / `\\\"read\\\"` | `Read` |\\n61\\t    /// | anything else | `None` |\\n62\\t    ///\\n63\\t    /// `tag:axon-agent` is an alias for `write` — the conventional tag for\\n64\\t    /// automated agent workloads that need read/write but not admin access.\\n65\\t    pub fn from_tag(tag: \u0026str) -\u003e Self {\\n66\\t        match tag {\\n67\\t            \\\"tag:axon-admin\\\" | \\\"tag:admin\\\" | \\\"admin\\\" =\u003e Role::Admin,\\n68\\t            \\\"tag:axon-write\\\" | \\\"tag:axon-agent\\\" | \\\"tag:write\\\" | \\\"write\\\" =\u003e Role::Write,\\n69\\t            \\\"tag:axon-read\\\" | \\\"tag:read\\\" | \\\"read\\\" =\u003e Role::Read,\\n70\\t            _ =\u003e Role::None,\\n71\\t        }\\n72\\t    }\\n73\\t\\n74\\t    /// Determine the highest-privilege role from a set of tags.\\n75\\t    pub fn from_tags(tags: \u0026[String]) -\u003e Self {\\n76\\t        tags.iter()\\n77\\t            .map(|t| Role::from_tag(t))\\n78\\t            .max()\\n79\\t            .unwrap_or(Role::None)\\n80\\t    }\\n81\\t}\\n82\\t\\n83\\timpl std::fmt::Display for Role {\\n84\\t    fn fmt(\u0026self, f: \u0026mut std::fmt::Formatter\u003c'_\u003e) -\u003e std::fmt::Result {\\n85\\t        match self {\\n86\\t            Role::None =\u003e write!(f, \\\"none\\\"),\\n87\\t            Role::Read =\u003e write!(f, \\\"read\\\"),\\n88\\t            Role::Write =\u003e write!(f, \\\"write\\\"),\\n89\\t            Role::Admin =\u003e write!(f, \\\"admin\\\"),\\n90\\t        }\\n91\\t    }\\n92\\t}\\n93\\t\\n94\\t/// The kind of operation being attempted.\\n95\\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]\\n96\\tpub enum Operation {\\n97\\t    /// Read an entity, query, traverse, audit.\\n98\\t    Read,\\n99\\t    /// Create, update, delete entities/links.\\n100\\t    Write,\\n101\\t    /// Drop collections, modify schemas, manage namespaces.\\n102\\t    Admin,\\n103\\t}\\n104\\t\\n105\\timpl Operation {\\n106\\t    /// The minimum role required for this operation.\\n107\\t    pub fn required_role(self) -\u003e Role {\\n108\\t        match self {\\n109\\t            Operation::Read =\u003e Role::Read,\\n110\\t            Operation::Write =\u003e Role::Write,\\n111\\t            Operation::Admin =\u003e Role::Admin,\\n112\\t        }\\n113\\t    }\\n114\\t}\\n115\\t\\n116\\t/// A simple field-equality filter used as an agent scope constraint\\n117\\t/// (FEAT-022 / ADR-016).\\n118\\t///\\n119\\t/// When attached to a [`CallerIdentity`], the agent guardrails layer rejects\\n120\\t/// any mutation whose target entity data does not satisfy\\n121\\t/// `data[field] == value`. V1 supports only field-equality predicates;\\n122\\t/// compound and range filters are deferred.\\n123\\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\\n124\\tpub struct EntityFilter {\\n125\\t    /// The top-level data field to compare.\\n126\\t    pub field: String,\\n127\\t    /// The required value for that field.\\n128\\t    pub value: serde_json::Value,\\n129\\t}\\n130\\t\\n131\\timpl EntityFilter {\\n132\\t    /// Convenience constructor.\\n133\\t    pub fn new(field: impl Into\u003cString\u003e, value: serde_json::Value) -\u003e Self {\\n134\\t        Self {\\n135\\t            field: field.into(),\\n136\\t            value,\\n137\\t        }\\n138\\t    }\\n139\\t\\n140\\t    /// Returns `true` when the JSON object `data` satisfies this filter.\\n141\\t    ///\\n142\\t    /// Returns `false` when `data` is not a JSON object, when the field is\\n143\\t    /// absent, or when the value does not equal [`Self::value`].\\n144\\t    pub fn matches(\u0026self, data: \u0026serde_json::Value) -\u003e bool {\\n145\\t        data.get(\u0026self.field).is_some_and(|v| v == \u0026self.value)\\n146\\t    }\\n147\\t}\\n148\\t\\n149\\t/// Identity context for a request.\\n150\\t///\\n151\\t/// Populated by the auth middleware from the identity provider.\\n152\\t/// In `--no-auth` mode, all requests get `CallerIdentity::anonymous()`.\\n153\\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]\\n154\\tpub struct CallerIdentity {\\n155\\t    /// Actor name for audit log entries.\\n156\\t    pub actor: String,\\n157\\t    /// The caller's effective role (highest privilege from all their tags).\\n158\\t    pub role: Role,\\n159\\t    /// Optional scope constraint enforced by the agent guardrails layer\\n160\\t    /// (FEAT-022, ADR-016). When `Some`, this caller may only mutate entities\\n161\\t    /// whose data matches the filter. `None` means no scope restriction.\\n162\\t    #[serde(default, skip_serializing_if = \\\"Option::is_none\\\")]\\n163\\t    pub entity_filter: Option\u003cEntityFilter\u003e,\\n164\\t}\\n165\\t\\n166\\timpl CallerIdentity {\\n167\\t    /// Create an anonymous identity with admin privileges (`--no-auth` mode).\\n168\\t    pub fn anonymous() -\u003e Self {\\n169\\t        Self {\\n170\\t            actor: \\\"anonymous\\\".into(),\\n171\\t            role: Role::Admin,\\n172\\t            entity_filter: None,\\n173\\t        }\\n174\\t    }\\n175\\t\\n176\\t    /// Create an identity from a name and role.\\n177\\t    pub fn new(actor: impl Into\u003cString\u003e, role: Role) -\u003e Self {\\n178\\t        Self {\\n179\\t            actor: actor.into(),\\n180\\t            role,\\n181\\t            entity_filter: None,\\n182\\t        }\\n183\\t    }\\n184\\t\\n185\\t    /// Attach an entity scope filter (builder style, FEAT-022).\\n186\\t    pub fn with_entity_filter(mut self, filter: EntityFilter) -\u003e Self {\\n187\\t        self.entity_filter = Some(filter);\\n188\\t        self\\n189\\t    }\\n190\\t\\n191\\t    /// Check whether this caller is authorized for the given operation.\\n192\\t    ///\\n193\\t    /// Returns `Ok(())` if authorized, or `Err(AxonError::InvalidOperation)`\\n194\\t    /// with a descriptive message if not.\\n195\\t    pub fn check(\u0026self, op: Operation) -\u003e Result\u003c(), AxonError\u003e {\\n196\\t        let required = op.required_role();\\n197\\t        if self.role \u003e= required {\\n198\\t            Ok(())\\n199\\t        } else {\\n200\\t            Err(AxonError::InvalidOperation(format!(\\n201\\t                \\\"permission denied: role '{}' cannot perform {:?} operations (requires '{}')\\\",\\n202\\t                self.role, op, required\\n203\\t            )))\\n204\\t        }\\n205\\t    }\\n206\\t\\n207\\t    /// Apply field-level masking to entity data based on mask policies.\\n208\\t    ///\\n209\\t    /// Admin users see all fields. For other roles, fields listed in a\\n210\\t    /// mask policy that requires a higher role than the caller's are\\n211\\t    /// removed from the data.\\n212\\t    pub fn apply_masks(\u0026self, data: \u0026mut serde_json::Value, policies: \u0026[MaskPolicy]) {\\n213\\t        if self.role \u003e= Role::Admin {\\n214\\t            return; // Admin sees all.\\n215\\t        }\\n216\\t        if let Some(obj) = data.as_object_mut() {\\n217\\t            for policy in policies {\\n218\\t                if self.role \u003c policy.min_role {\\n219\\t                    obj.remove(\u0026policy.field);\\n220\\t                }\\n221\\t            }\\n222\\t        }\\n223\\t    }\\n224\\t}\\n225\\t\\n226\\t/// A field-level mask policy (US-046, FEAT-012).\\n227\\t///\\n228\\t/// Specifies that a field should be hidden from callers whose role is\\n229\\t/// below `min_role`. Admin always sees all fields.\\n230\\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\\n231\\tpub struct MaskPolicy {\\n232\\t    /// The field name to mask.\\n233\\t    pub field: String,\\n234\\t    /// Minimum role required to see this field.\\n235\\t    pub min_role: Role,\\n236\\t}\\n237\\t\\n238\\t// ── Attribute-based write control (US-047, FEAT-012) ────────────────────────\\n239\\t\\n240\\t/// Per-collection write policy for attribute-based access control (ABAC).\\n241\\t///\\n242\\t/// Stored in the `__axon_policies__` pseudo-collection. Defines:\\n243\\t/// - Minimum role required to write to this collection\\n244\\t/// - Fields that are immutable after creation\\n245\\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\\n246\\tpub struct WritePolicy {\\n247\\t    /// Collection this policy applies to.\\n248\\t    pub collection: String,\\n249\\t    /// Minimum role required for write operations.\\n250\\t    pub min_write_role: Role,\\n251\\t    /// Fields that cannot be modified after the initial create.\\n252\\t    #[serde(default)]\\n253\\t    pub immutable_fields: Vec\u003cString\u003e,\\n254\\t}\\n255\\t\\n256\\timpl WritePolicy {\\n257\\t    /// Check if a caller has sufficient role to write to this collection.\\n258\\t    pub fn check_write(\u0026self, caller: \u0026CallerIdentity) -\u003e Result\u003c(), AxonError\u003e {\\n259\\t        if caller.role \u003e= self.min_write_role {\\n260\\t            Ok(())\\n261\\t        } else {\\n262\\t            Err(AxonError::InvalidOperation(format!(\\n263\\t                \\\"write policy for '{}': role '{}' insufficient (requires '{}')\\\",\\n264\\t                self.collection, caller.role, self.min_write_role\\n265\\t            )))\\n266\\t        }\\n267\\t    }\\n268\\t\\n269\\t    /// Check if any immutable fields have been modified.\\n270\\t    ///\\n271\\t    /// Returns the list of field names that were illegally modified.\\n272\\t    pub fn check_immutable_fields(\\n273\\t        \u0026self,\\n274\\t        old_data: \u0026serde_json::Value,\\n275\\t        new_data: \u0026serde_json::Value,\\n276\\t    ) -\u003e Vec\u003cString\u003e {\\n277\\t        let mut violations = Vec::new();\\n278\\t        for field in \u0026self.immutable_fields {\\n279\\t            let old_val = old_data.get(field);\\n280\\t            let new_val = new_data.get(field);\\n281\\t            // If the field existed before and is now different or missing, it's a violation.\\n282\\t            if old_val.is_some() \u0026\u0026 old_val != new_val {\\n283\\t                violations.push(field.clone());\\n284\\t            }\\n285\\t        }\\n286\\t        violations\\n287\\t    }\\n288\\t}\\n289\\t\\n290\\t// ── Database-scoped access control (US-038, FEAT-014) ────────────────────────\\n291\\t\\n292\\t/// A grant that scopes a role to a specific database.\\n293\\t///\\n294\\t/// Without a grant, users cannot access a database (unless they have a\\n295\\t/// wildcard `*` grant or admin role).\\n296\\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\\n297\\tpub struct DatabaseGrant {\\n298\\t    /// The actor (user/node) this grant applies to. `\\\"*\\\"` means all users.\\n299\\t    pub actor: String,\\n300\\t    /// The database name. `\\\"*\\\"` means all databases.\\n301\\t    pub database: String,\\n302\\t    /// The role granted for this database.\\n303\\t    pub role: Role,\\n304\\t}\\n305\\t\\n306\\t/// Registry of database-scoped grants.\\n307\\t#[derive(Debug, Clone, Default, Serialize, Deserialize)]\\n308\\tpub struct GrantRegistry {\\n309\\t    grants: Vec\u003cDatabaseGrant\u003e,\\n310\\t}\\n311\\t\\n312\\timpl GrantRegistry {\\n313\\t    /// Create a new empty grant registry.\\n314\\t    pub fn new() -\u003e Self {\\n315\\t        Self::default()\\n316\\t    }\\n317\\t\\n318\\t    /// Add a grant.\\n319\\t    pub fn add(\u0026mut self, grant: DatabaseGrant) {\\n320\\t        self.grants.push(grant);\\n321\\t    }\\n322\\t\\n323\\t    /// Remove all grants for an actor on a database.\\n324\\t    pub fn revoke(\u0026mut self, actor: \u0026str, database: \u0026str) {\\n325\\t        self.grants\\n326\\t            .retain(|g| g.actor != actor || g.database != database);\\n327\\t    }\\n328\\t\\n329\\t    /// Resolve the effective role for an actor on a database.\\n330\\t    ///\\n331\\t    /// Checks grants in order: exact match, then wildcard actor, then\\n332\\t    /// wildcard database. Returns the highest-privilege matching role.\\n333\\t    pub fn effective_role(\u0026self, actor: \u0026str, database: \u0026str) -\u003e Role {\\n334\\t        self.grants\\n335\\t            .iter()\\n336\\t            .filter(|g| {\\n337\\t                (g.actor == actor || g.actor == \\\"*\\\")\\n338\\t                    \u0026\u0026 (g.database == database || g.database == \\\"*\\\")\\n339\\t            })\\n340\\t            .map(|g| g.role)\\n341\\t            .max()\\n342\\t            .unwrap_or(Role::None)\\n343\\t    }\\n344\\t\\n345\\t    /// Check if an actor can perform an operation on a database.\\n346\\t    pub fn check(\\n347\\t        \u0026self,\\n348\\t        actor: \u0026str,\\n349\\t        database: \u0026str,\\n350\\t        operation: Operation,\\n351\\t    ) -\u003e Result\u003c(), AxonError\u003e {\\n352\\t        let role = self.effective_role(actor, database);\\n353\\t        if role \u003e= operation.required_role() {\\n354\\t            Ok(())\\n355\\t        } else {\\n356\\t            Err(AxonError::InvalidOperation(format!(\\n357\\t                \\\"no grant for actor '{actor}' on database '{database}' with sufficient role (has '{role}', needs '{}')\\\",\\n358\\t                operation.required_role()\\n359\\t            )))\\n360\\t        }\\n361\\t    }\\n362\\t\\n363\\t    /// List all grants.\\n364\\t    pub fn list(\u0026self) -\u003e \u0026[DatabaseGrant] {\\n365\\t        \u0026self.grants\\n366\\t    }\\n367\\t}\\n368\\t\\n369\\t#[cfg(test)]\\n370\\tmod tests {\\n371\\t    use super::*;\\n372\\t\\n373\\t    #[test]\\n374\\t    fn role_ordering() {\\n375\\t        assert!(Role::Admin \u003e Role::Write);\\n376\\t        assert!(Role::Write \u003e Role::Read);\\n377\\t        assert!(Role::Read \u003e Role::None);\\n378\\t    }\\n379\    .execute(\\n                \\\"DELETE FROM schema_versions\\n                 WHERE collection = ?1 AND database_name = ?2 AND schema_name = ?3\\\",\\n                params![\\n                    collection.as_str(),\\n                    key.namespace.database.as_str(),\\n                    key.namespace.schema.as_str()\\n                ],\\n            )\\n            .map_err(|e| AxonError::Storage(e.to_string()))?;\\n        self.conn()?\\n            .execute(\\n                \\\"DELETE FROM collections\\n                 WHERE name = ?1 AND database_name = ?2 AND schema_name = ?3\\\",\\n                params![\\n                    collection.as_str(),\\n                    key.namespace.database.as_str(),\\n                    key.namespace.schema.as_str()\\n                ],\\n            )\\n            .map_err(|e| AxonError::Storage(e.to_string()))?;\\n        Ok(())\\n    }\\n\\n    fn list_collections(\u0026self) -\u003e Result\u003cVec\u003cCollectionId\u003e, AxonError\u003e {\\n        let conn = self.conn()?;\\n        let mut stmt = conn\\n            .prepare_cached(\\n                \\\"SELECT name FROM collections\\n                 ORDER BY database_name ASC, schema_name ASC, name ASC\\\",\\n            )\\n            .map_err(|e| AxonError::Storage(e.to_string()))?;\\n\\n        let rows = stmt\\n            .query_map([], |row| row.get::\u003c_, String\u003e(0))\\n            .map_err(|e| AxonError::Storage(e.to_string()))?;\\n\\n        let mut names = Vec::new();\\n        for row in rows {\\n            names.push(CollectionId::new(\\n                row.map_err(|e| AxonError::Storage(e.to_string()))?,\\n            ));\\n        }\\n        Ok(names)\\n    }\\n\\n    fn collection_registered_in_namespace(\\n        \u0026self,\\n        collection: \u0026CollectionId,\\n        namespace: \u0026Namespace,\\n    ) -\u003e Result\u003cbool, AxonError\u003e {\\n        self.collection_exists_in_namespace(collection, namespace)\\n    }\\n}\\n\\n#[cfg(test)]\\nmod tests {\\n    use super::*;\\n    use axon_core::types::Link;\\n    use serde_json::json;\\n    use tempfile::NamedTempFile;\\n\\n    fn tasks() -\u003e CollectionId {\\n        CollectionId::new(\\\"tasks\\\")\\n    }\\n\\n    fn entity(id: \u0026str) -\u003e Entity {\\n        Entity::new(tasks(), EntityId::new(id), json!({\\\"title\\\": id}))\\n    }\\n\\n    fn store() -\u003e SqliteStorageAdapter {\\n        SqliteStorageAdapter::open_in_memory().expect(\\\"test operation should succeed\\\")\\n    }\\n\\n    fn register_unique_namespaced_collection(\\n        store: \u0026mut SqliteStorageAdapter,\\n        qualified: \u0026CollectionId,\\n    ) -\u003e (Namespace, CollectionId) {\\n        let (namespace, bare_collection) = Namespace::parse(qualified.as_str());\\n        let bare_collection = CollectionId::new(bare_collection);\\n\\n        store\\n            .create_database(namespace.database.as_str())\\n            .expect(\\\"database create should succeed\\\");\\n        store\\n            .create_namespace(\u0026namespace)\\n            .expect(\\\"namespace create should succeed\\\");\\n        store\\n            .register_collection_in_namespace(\u0026bare_collection, \u0026namespace)\\n            .expect(\\\"collection register should succeed\\\");\\n\\n        (namespace, bare_collection)\\n    }\\n\\n    fn legacy_collection_views_db(collection: \u0026CollectionId, template: \u0026str) -\u003e NamedTempFile {\\n        let file = NamedTempFile::new().expect(\\\"test temp db should be created\\\");\\n        let conn = Connection::open(file.path()).expect(\\\"test temp db connection should be opened\\\");\\n        conn.execute_batch(\\n            \\\"PRAGMA foreign_keys = ON;\\n            CREATE TABLE collections (\\n                name TEXT NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY\\n            );\\n            CREATE TABLE collection_views (\\n                collection        TEXT NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY,\\n                version           INTEGER NOT NULL,\\n                view_json         TEXT NOT NULL,\\n                updated_at_ns     INTEGER NOT NULL,\\n                updated_by        TEXT\\n            );\\\",\\n        )\\n        .expect(\\\"legacy schema should be created\\\");\\n        let view_json = serde_json::to_string(\u0026CollectionView::new(collection.clone(), template))\\n            .expect(\\\"legacy collection view should serialize\\\");\\n        conn.execute(\\n            \\\"INSERT INTO collections (name) VALUES (?1)\\\",\\n            params![collection.as_str()],\\n        )\\n        .expect(\\\"legacy collection should be inserted\\\");\\n        conn.execute(\\n            \\\"INSERT INTO collection_views (collection, version, view_json, updated_at_ns, updated_by)\\n             VALUES (?1, ?2, ?3, ?4, ?5)\\\",\\n            params![collection.as_str(), 1_i64, view_json, 0_i64, Option::\u003c\u0026str\u003e::None],\\n        )\\n        .expect(\\\"legacy collection view should be inserted\\\");\\n        file\\n    }\\n\\n    #[test]\\n    fn create_entity() {\\n        let mut s = store();\\n        s.put(entity(\\\"t-001\\\"))\\n            .expect(\\\"test operation should succeed\\\");\\n        assert_eq!(s.count(\u0026tasks()).expect(\\\"test operation should succeed\\\"), 1);\\n    }\\n\\n    #[test]\\n    fn default_database_and_namespace_exist_on_open() {\\n        let s = store();\\n        assert_eq!(\\n            s.list_databases().expect(\\\"catalog query should succeed\\\"),\\n            vec![\\\"default\\\".to_string()]\\n        );\\n        assert_eq!(\\n            s.list_namespaces(\\\"default\\\")\\n                .expect(\\\"namespace query should succeed\\\"),\\n            vec![\\\"default\\\".to_string()]\\n        );\\n    }\\n\\n    #[test]\\n    fn database_and_namespace_catalog_persist_across_reopen() {\\n        let file = NamedTempFile::new().expect(\\\"test temp db should be created\\\");\\n        let path = file.path().to_string_lossy().into_owned();\\n\\n        {\\n            let mut s = SqliteStorageAdapter::open(\u0026path).expect(\\\"initial open should succeed\\\");\\n            s.create_database(\\\"prod\\\")\\n                .expect(\\\"database create should succeed\\\");\\n            s.create_namespace(\u0026Namespace::new(\\\"prod\\\", \\\"billing\\\"))\\n                .expect(\\\"namespace create should succeed\\\");\\n        }\\n\\n        let reopened = SqliteStorageAdapter::open(\u0026path).expect(\\\"reopen should succeed\\\");\\n        assert!(reopened\\n            .list_databases()\\n            .expect(\\\"catalog query should succeed\\\")\\n            .iter()\\n            .any(|database| database == \\\"prod\\\"));\\n        assert!(reopened\\n            .list_namespaces(\\\"prod\\\")\\n            .expect(\\\"namespace query should succeed\\\")\\n            .iter()\\n            .any(|schema| schema == \\\"billing\\\"));\\n    }\\n\\n    #[test]\\n    fn namespace_catalogs_allow_same_name_without_cross_drop() {\\n        let mut s = store();\\n        let invoices = CollectionId::new(\\\"invoices\\\");\\n        let billing = Namespace::new(\\\"prod\\\", \\\"billing\\\");\\n        let engineering = Namespace::new(\\\"prod\\\", \\\"engineering\\\");\\n\\n        s.create_database(\\\"prod\\\")\\n            .expect(\\\"database create should succeed\\\");\\n        s.create_namespace(\u0026billing)\\n            .expect(\\\"billing namespace create should succeed\\\");\\n        s.create_namespace(\u0026engineering)\\n            .expect(\\\"engineering namespace create should succeed\\\");\\n\\n        s.register_collection_in_namespace(\u0026invoices, \u0026Namespace::default_ns())\\n            .expect(\\\"default collection register should succeed\\\");\\n        s.register_collection_in_namespace(\u0026invoices, \u0026billing)\\n            .expect(\\\"billing collection register should succeed\\\");\\n        s.register_collection_in_namespace(\u0026invoices, \u0026engineering)\\n            .expect(\\\"engineering collection register should succeed\\\");\\n\\n        assert_eq!(\\n            s.list_namespace_collections(\u0026billing)\\n                .expect(\\\"billing list should succeed\\\"),\\n            vec![invoices.clone()]\\n        );\\n        assert_eq!(\\n            s.list_namespace_collections(\u0026engineering)\\n                .expect(\\\"engineering list should succeed\\\"),\\n            vec![invoices.clone()]\\n        );\\n\\n        s.drop_namespace(\u0026billing)\\n            .expect(\\\"billing drop should succeed\\\");\\n        assert_eq!(\\n            s.list_namespace_collections(\u0026engineering)\\n                .expect(\\\"engineering list should survive billing drop\\\"),\\n            vec![invoices.clone()]\\n        );\\n        assert_eq!(\\n            s.list_namespace_collections(\u0026Namespace::default_ns())\\n                .expect(\\\"default list should survive billing drop\\\"),\\n            vec![invoices.clone()]\\n        );\\n\\n        s.drop_database(\\\"prod\\\").expect(\\\"prod drop should succeed\\\");\\n        assert_eq!(\\n            s.list_namespace_collections(\u0026Namespace::default_ns())\\n                .expect(\\\"default list should survive prod drop\\\"),\\n            vec![invoices]\\n        );\\n    }\\n\\n    #[test]\\n    fn drop_namespace_purges_entities_for_removed_collections() {\\n        let mut s = store();\\n        let billing = Namespace::new(\\\"prod\\\", \\\"billing\\\");\\n        let engineering = Namespace::new(\\\"prod\\\", \\\"engineering\\\");\\n        let invoices = CollectionId::new(\\\"invoices\\\");\\n        let ledger = CollectionId::new(\\\"ledger\\\");\\n\\n        s.create_database(\\\"prod\\\")\\n            .expect(\\\"database create should succeed\\\");\\n        s.create_namespace(\u0026billing)\\n            .expect(\\\"billing namespace create should succeed\\\");\\n        s.create_namespace(\u0026engineering)\\n            .expect(\\\"engineering namespace create should succeed\\\");\\n        s.register_collection_in_namespace(\u0026invoices, \u0026billing)\\n            .expect(\\\"billing collection register should succeed\\\");\\n        s.register_collection_in_namespace(\u0026ledger, \u0026engineering)\\n            .expect(\\\"engineering collection register should succeed\\\");\\n        s.put(Entity::new(\\n            invoices.clone(),\\n            EntityId::new(\\\"inv-001\\\"),\\n            json!({\\\"title\\\": \\\"invoice\\\"}),\\n        ))\\n        .expect(\\\"billing entity put should succeed\\\");\\n        s.put(Entity::new(\\n            ledger.clone(),\\n            EntityId::new(\\\"led-001\\\"),\\n            json!({\\\"title\\\": \\\"ledger\\\"}),\\n        ))\\n        .expect(\\\"engineering entity put should succeed\\\");\\n\\n        s.drop_namespace(\u0026billing)\\n            .expect(\\\"billing drop should succeed\\\");\\n\\n        assert!(\\n            s.get(\u0026invoices, \u0026EntityId::new(\\\"inv-001\\\"))\\n                .expect(\\\"billing entity lookup should succeed\\\")\\n                .is_none(),\\n            \\\"dropped namespace entities must be purged\\\"\\n        );\\n        assert!(\\n            s.get(\u0026ledger, \u0026EntityId::new(\\\"led-001\\\"))\\n                .expect(\\\"surviving entity lookup should succeed\\\")\\n                .is_some(),\\n            \\\"entities in other namespaces must survive\\\"\\n        );\\n    }\\n\\n    #[test]\\n    fn drop_namespace_keeps_same_named_entities_in_surviving_namespaces() {\\n        let mut s = store();\\n        let billing = Namespace::new(\\\"prod\\\", \\\"billing\\\");\\n        let engineering = Namespace::new(\\\"prod\\\", \\\"engineering\\\");\\n        let invoices = CollectionId::new(\\\"invoices\\\");\\n        let ledger = CollectionId::new(\\\"ledger\\\");\\n\\n        s.create_database(\\\"prod\\\")\\n            .expect(\\\"database create should succeed\\\");\\n        s.create_namespace(\u0026billing)\\n            .expect(\\\"billing namespace create should succeed\\\");\\n        s.create_namespace(\u0026engineering)\\n            .expect(\\\"engineering namespace create should succeed\\\");\\n        s.register_collection_in_namespace(\u0026invoices, \u0026Namespace::default_ns())\\n            .expect(\\\"default collection register should succeed\\\");\\n        s.register_collection_in_namespace(\u0026invoices, \u0026billing)\\n            .expect(\\\"billing collection register should succeed\\\");\\n        s.register_collection_in_namespace(\u0026invoices, \u0026engineering)\\n            .expect(\\\"engineering collection register should succeed\\\");\\n        s.register_collection_in_namespace(\u0026ledger, \u0026billing)\\n            .expect(\\\"billing ledger register should succeed\\\");\\n        s.put(Entity::new(\\n            invoices.clone(),\\n            EntityId::new(\\\"inv-default-001\\\"),\\n            json!({\\\"title\\\": \\\"default invoice\\\"}),\\n        ))\\n        .expect(\\\"default entity put should succeed\\\");\\n        s.put(Entity::new(\\n            ledger.clone(),\\n            EntityId::new(\\\"led-billing-001\\\"),\\n            json!({\\\"title\\\": \\\"billing ledger\\\"}),\\n        ))\\n        .expect(\\\"billing ledger put should succeed\\\");\\n\\n        s.drop_namespace(\u0026billing)\\n            .expect(\\\"billing drop should succeed\\\");\\n\\n        assert!(\\n            s.get(\u0026invoices, \u0026EntityId::new(\\\"inv-default-001\\\"))\\n                .expect(\\\"default entity lookup should succeed\\\")\\n                .is_some(),\\n            \\\"same-named entities in surviving namespaces must be preserved\\\"\\n        );\\n        assert!(\\n            s.get(\u0026ledger, \u0026EntityId::new(\\\"led-billing-001\\\"))\\n                .expect(\\\"billing ledger lookup should succeed\\\")\\n                .is_none(),\\n            \\\"entities in the dropped namespace must be purged\\\"\\n        );\\n    }\\n\\n    #[test]\\n    fn drop_namespace_purges_links_for_removed_collections() {\\n        let mut s = store();\\n        let billing = Namespace::new(\\\"prod\\\", \\\"billing\\\");\\n        let engineering = Namespace::new(\\\"prod\\\", \\\"engineering\\\");\\n        let invoices = CollectionId::new(\\\"prod.billing.invoices\\\");\\n        let ledger = CollectionId::new(\\\"prod.engineering.ledger\\\");\\n        let keep = CollectionId::new(\\\"keep\\\");\\n        let archive = CollectionId::new(\\\"archive\\\");\\n\\n        s.create_database(\\\"prod\\\")\\n            .expect(\\\"database create should succeed\\\");\\n        s.create_namespace(\u0026billing)\\n            .expect(\\\"billing namespace create should succeed\\\");\\n        s.create_namespace(\u0026engineering)\\n            .expect(\\\"engineering namespace create should succeed\\\");\\n        s.register_collection_in_namespace(\u0026CollectionId::new(\\\"invoices\\\"), \u0026billing)\\n            .expect(\\\"billing collection register should succeed\\\");\\n        s.register_collection_in_namespace(\u0026CollectionId::new(\\\"ledger\\\"), \u0026engineering)\\n            .expect(\\\"engineering collection register should succeed\\\");\\n        s.register_collection(\u0026keep)\\n            .expect(\\\"default collection register should succeed\\\");\\n        s.register_collection(\u0026archive)\\n            .expect(\\\"archive collection register should succeed\\\");\\n        for entity in [\\n            Entity::new(\\n                invoices.clone(),\\n                EntityId::new(\\\"inv-001\\\"),\\n                json!({\\\"title\\\": \\\"invoice\\\"}),\\n            ),\\n            Entity::new(\\n                ledger.clone(),\\n                EntityId::new(\\\"led-001\\\"),\\n                json!({\\\"title\\\": \\\"ledger\\\"}),\\n            ),\\n            Entity::new(\\n                keep.clone(),\\n                EntityId::new(\\\"keep-001\\\"),\\n                json!({\\\"title\\\": \\\"keep\\\"}),\\n            ),\\n            Entity::new(\\n                archive.clone(),\\n                EntityId::new(\\\"arc-001\\\"),\\n                json!({\\\"title\\\": \\\"archive\\\"}),\\n            ),\\n        ] {\\n            s.put(entity).expect(\\\"entity put should succeed\\\");\\n        }\\n\\n        for link in [\\n            Link {\\n                source_collection: invoices.clone(),\\n                source_id: EntityId::new(\\\"inv-001\\\"),\\n                target_collection: ledger.clone(),\\n                target_id: EntityId::new(\\\"led-001\\\"),\\n                link_type: \\\"relates-to\\\".into(),\\n                metadata: serde_json::Value::Null,\\n            },\\n            Link {\\n                source_collection: keep.clone(),\\n                source_id: EntityId::new(\\\"keep-001\\\"),\\n                target_collection: invoices.clone(),\\n                target_id: EntityId::new(\\\"inv-001\\\"),\\n                link_type: \\\"references\\\".into(),\\n                metadata: serde_json::Value::Null,\\n            },\\n            Link {\\n                source_collection: keep.clone(),\\n                source_id: EntityId::new(\\\"keep-001\\\"),\\n                target_collection: archive.clone(),\\n                target_id: EntityId::new(\\\"arc-001\\\"),\\n                link_type: \\\"references\\\".into(),\\n                metadata: serde_json::Value::Null,\\n            },\\n        ] {\\n            s.put_link(\u0026link).expect(\\\"link put should succeed\\\");\\n        }\\n\\n        s.drop_namespace(\u0026billing)\\n            .expect(\\\"billing drop should succeed\\\");\\n\\n        assert!(\\n            s.list_inbound_links(\u0026ledger, \u0026EntityId::new(\\\"led-001\\\"), None)\\n                .expect(\\\"ledger inbound links should load\\\")\\n                .is_empty(),\\n            \\\"links from removed collections must be purged\\\"\\n        );\\n        let keep_links = s\\n            .list_outbound_links(\u0026keep, \u0026EntityId::new(\\\"keep-001\\\"), None)\\n            .expect(\\\"keep outbound links should load\\\");\\n        assert_eq!(keep_links.len(), 1);\\n        assert_eq!(keep_links[0].target_collection, archive);\\n    }\\n\\n    #[test]\\n    fn drop_database_purges_entities_for_removed_collections() {\\n        let mut s = store();\\n        let analytics = Namespace::new(\\\"prod\\\", \\\"analytics\\\");\\n        let orders = CollectionId::new(\\\"orders\\\");\\n        let rollups = CollectionId::new(\\\"rollups\\\");\\n        let keep = CollectionId::new(\\\"keep\\\");\\n\\n        s.create_database(\\\"prod\\\")\\n            .expect(\\\"database create should succeed\\\");\\n        s.create_namespace(\u0026analytics)\\n            .expect(\\\"analytics namespace create should succeed\\\");\\n        s.register_collection_in_namespace(\u0026orders, \u0026Namespace::new(\\\"prod\\\", \\\"default\\\"))\\n            .expect(\\\"prod default collection register should succeed\\\");\\n        s.register_collection_in_namespace(\u0026rollups, \u0026analytics)\\n            .expect(\\\"analytics collection register should succeed\\\");\\n        s.register_collection_in_namespace(\u0026keep, \u0026Namespace::default_ns())\\n            .expect(\\\"default collection register should succeed\\\");\\n        s.put(Entity::new(\\n            orders.clone(),\\n            EntityId::new(\\\"ord-001\\\"),\\n            json!({\\\"title\\\": \\\"order\\\"}),\\n        ))\\n        .expect(\\\"prod default entity put should succeed\\\");\\n        s.put(Entity::new(\\n            rollups.clone(),\\n            EntityId::new(\\\"sum-001\\\"),\\n            json!({\\\"title\\\": \\\"rollup\\\"}),\\n        ))\\n        .expect(\\\"analytics entity put should succeed\\\");\\n        s.put(Entity::new(\\n            keep.clone(),\\n            EntityId::new(\\\"keep-001\\\"),\\n            json!({\\\"title\\\": \\\"keep\\\"}),\\n        ))\\n        .expect(\\\"default entity put should succeed\\\");\\n\\n        s.drop_database(\\\"prod\\\")\\n            .expect(\\\"database drop should succeed\\\");\\n\\n        assert!(\\n            s.get(\u0026orders, \u0026EntityId::new(\\\"ord-001\\\"))\\n                .expect(\\\"orders lookup should succeed\\\")\\n                .is_none(),\\n            \\\"dropped database entities must be purged\\\"\\n        );\\n        assert!(\\n            s.get(\u0026rollups, \u0026EntityId::new(\\\"sum-001\\\"))\\n                .expect(\\\"rollups lookup should succeed\\\")\\n                .is_none(),\\n            \\\"all namespace entities in the dropped database must be purged\\\"\\n       